61
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:33,199
One key fact in the rise of popularity of the biscuit is meal times.

62
00:03:33,199 --> 00:03:37,839
Before the Industrial Revolution, people have a later breakfast and an earlier supper.

63
00:03:37,839 --> 00:03:42,639
By the end of the Industrial Revolution, breakfast is much earlier.

64
00:03:42,639 --> 00:03:44,000
The evening meal is much later.

65
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:49,039
So you've got this big gap of time where people need sustenance.

66
00:03:49,039 --> 00:03:54,159
And so lunch comes to greater prominence and tea time comes to greater prominence and snacking.

67
00:03:54,159 --> 00:03:57,359
So there's this great opportunity for really biscuits,

68
00:03:57,359 --> 00:04:00,959
something small, something ready, something easily consumable,

69
00:04:00,959 --> 00:04:03,119
not expensive, you know, a bit of a sugar rush.

70
00:04:04,879 --> 00:04:08,560
Right. So it was the Industrial Revolution that led to the rise.

71
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:11,279
That's the increase in the popularity of biscuits.

72
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:15,360
Because the time between breakfast and dinner in the evening increased,

73
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:19,199
people got hungry and they needed food to give them energy.

74
00:04:19,199 --> 00:04:21,519
What Anastasia called sustenance.

75
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:25,439
So this is when smaller meals, such as lunch or tea,

76
00:04:25,439 --> 00:04:28,079
became important or more well known,

77
00:04:28,079 --> 00:04:29,519
it had greater prominence.

78
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:32,800
And this included snacking on biscuits.

79
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:36,800
